1
00:00:01,270 --> 00:00:07,810
Well, we continue studying the Sermon on the Mount, and I've really enjoyed this series.

2
00:00:07,950 --> 00:00:11,910
It's challenged me in many ways, and I've read it a number of times, and it was still

3
00:00:11,910 --> 00:00:13,330
wonderful to really dig in.

4
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:18,220
As we've been looking at this, we all have been discovering that we want to be good people,

5
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:25,290
and we've discovered that that kind of goodness is found in the kingdom of God, what we're

6
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:30,400
calling the upside-down kingdom, because it's upside-down to the way that the world

7
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:31,140
operates.

8
00:00:32,370 --> 00:00:36,330
It's different from the values and the perspectives of our world.

9
00:00:36,990 --> 00:00:39,090
And when you live inside of God's kingdom,

10
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:44,020
then you evidence that kind of goodness that we're striving for

11
00:00:44,020 --> 00:00:48,120
because it is God who fills you and begins to do that through you.

12
00:00:49,070 --> 00:00:50,530
It's wonderful to live like that.

13
00:00:51,890 --> 00:00:54,970
And so now we continue to look at some topics that Jesus covers

14
00:00:54,970 --> 00:00:57,000
as we look at his kingdom.

15
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,140
The first one is this issue of truth.

16
00:01:00,530 --> 00:01:02,230
And he says in Matthew 5.33,

17
00:01:03,660 --> 00:01:03,940
He says,

18
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,420
Again you have heard the law of Moses says,

19
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:08,600
Do not break your vows.

20
00:01:09,620 --> 00:01:11,900
You must carry out the vows you have made to the Lord.

21
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:12,960
But I say,

22
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:15,180
Don't make any vows.

23
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:18,040
If you say by heaven,

24
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:21,300
it's a sacred vow because heaven is God's throne.

25
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:23,120
And if you say by the earth,

26
00:01:23,260 --> 00:01:26,760
it is a sacred vow because the earth is his footstool.

27
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:28,900
And don't swear by Jerusalem,

28
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:32,320
for Jerusalem is the city of the great king.

29
00:01:33,180 --> 00:01:37,180
Don't even swear by my head, for you can't turn one hair white or black.

30
00:01:37,860 --> 00:01:42,040
Just say a simple, yes, I will, or no, I won't.

31
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:46,060
Your word is enough to strengthen your promise with a vow

32
00:01:46,060 --> 00:01:48,860
that shows that something is wrong.

33
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:56,540
Now, you've all heard the famous oath that children utter all the time.

34
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:03,520
Cross my heart, hope to die, stick a needle where?

35
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:06,380
That's gross.

36
00:02:08,230 --> 00:02:11,930
But in the world of children, this is very important.

37
00:02:12,070 --> 00:02:16,050
When you utter those words, everything stops.

38
00:02:16,210 --> 00:02:18,170
We know this is the truth.

39
00:02:18,290 --> 00:02:19,230
This is serious.

40
00:02:20,290 --> 00:02:26,950
But you also know in the world of children that you can nullify the cross my heart, stick a needle routine by doing what?

41
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:28,680
Cross the fingers.

42
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:33,180
See, when you cross the fingers, everything you've just said is out.

43
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:34,600
And you can do whatever it is you want.

44
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,680
Say whatever you want as long as the fingers are crossed.

45
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,560
That's how the world of children operates.

46
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:41,200
There are certain rules and certain oaths and certain language

47
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:44,740
and certain mechanisms to undo some of those things.

48
00:02:45,580 --> 00:02:48,240
Makes perfect sense if you're between the ages of 5 and 10.

49
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:54,160
Unfortunately, though, adults do similar kinds of things as well.

50
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:59,060
Sometimes adults use certain kinds of language to skirt around truth,

51
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:01,600
to say certain things and mean something else.

52
00:03:01,980 --> 00:03:05,660
Sometimes we find ways to undo what it is that we've said.

53
00:03:07,010 --> 00:03:10,550
You see, an oath truly is a solemn statement affirmed before God.

54
00:03:10,990 --> 00:03:15,810
And whenever you're talking about invoking the deity, the truth must be spoken.

55
00:03:16,450 --> 00:03:18,370
In Jesus' day, oaths were a big deal.

56
00:03:19,130 --> 00:03:22,530
Religious leaders were always making oaths and swearing by all kinds of things

57
00:03:22,530 --> 00:03:26,600
to impress people, to validate what they were saying.

58
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:31,280
They were also famous for finding loopholes, just like the children do today,

59
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,140
the crossing of the fingers. It's the same idea.

60
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:36,880
And Jesus cuts right through this.

61
00:03:37,950 --> 00:03:42,390
Jesus says, it doesn't matter whether you said certain things or crossing your fingers.

62
00:03:42,710 --> 00:03:49,690
The reality is, Jesus is the truth, and we as his followers must be committed to the truth.

63
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:55,560
The challenge for us is, so friends, speak the truth.

64
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:58,200
Yes or no is all that's needed.

65
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,600
Stand behind your words.

66
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:03,260
We don't need to go through all that other shenanigans.

67
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:05,560
Be forthright in your character.

68
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:08,360
Why? Because Jesus is the truth.

69
00:04:10,010 --> 00:04:14,770
See, we live in a culture now that radio and television and film is famous for what?

70
00:04:14,810 --> 00:04:15,770
What's that new profession?

71
00:04:15,930 --> 00:04:18,410
The spin doctor, right?

72
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:24,990
What does a spin doctor do but try and spin things, certain elements of truth to make

73
00:04:24,990 --> 00:04:27,130
you think certain things, not show you the whole picture?

74
00:04:28,230 --> 00:04:29,790
Tilt the truth to fit an agenda.

75
00:04:30,690 --> 00:04:32,110
No wonder we don't trust each other.

76
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:34,010
There's always spin in the world.

77
00:04:34,090 --> 00:04:35,970
Which way is this story being spun?

78
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,280
And Jesus is challenging that kind of thinking,

79
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:40,880
going straight up and saying,

80
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:43,620
disciples of Jesus Christ are to live differently.

81
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,880
They're to be about truth.

82
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,540
There's a reason for that, too.

83
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:53,100
Not only is it because Jesus is the truth,

84
00:04:54,150 --> 00:04:57,310
but do you realize that honoring truth honors people?

85
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,100
Do you realize that?

86
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:02,400
That when you speak the truth, you're honoring the person

87
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:05,140
as a person made in the image of God

88
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:07,660
who deserves to hear the truth.

89
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:11,000
You honor people by speaking truth.

90
00:05:13,220 --> 00:05:15,960
See, in Jesus' day, they used to manipulate people

91
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:21,160
by swearing oaths and doing all kinds of these linguistic shenanigans.

92
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:24,680
And it was really a manipulative technique, a manipulative tactic.

93
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:29,950
And see, it fundamentally flawed because it doesn't honor people.

94
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:33,200
It doesn't honor people as created in the image of God.

95
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,880
That's not God's ethic.

96
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:40,440
Dallas Wood has a great quote I've shared from The Divine Conspiracy.

97
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:41,780
He writes this,

98
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:46,570
Kingdom rightness respects the sole need of human beings

99
00:05:46,570 --> 00:05:49,750
to make their judgments and their decisions

100
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:52,870
solely from what they have concluded is best.

101
00:05:54,180 --> 00:05:55,580
It's a vital biological need.

102
00:05:55,860 --> 00:05:58,780
We do not thrive, nor does our character develop well,

103
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,980
when that need is not respected,

104
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:04,380
and it thwarts the purpose of God in our creation.

105
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,780
Friends, when you live in God's kingdom,

106
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:10,990
and when you love God and love others as yourself,

107
00:06:10,990 --> 00:06:14,010
to love others as yourself is to respect them

108
00:06:14,010 --> 00:06:16,870
and treat them as creatures made in the image of God

109
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:19,730
with God's likeness somehow stamped on them.

110
00:06:20,270 --> 00:06:22,350
And you don't treat them as a means to an end.

111
00:06:22,850 --> 00:06:25,530
You speak truth to them because you respect them

112
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:29,370
and you respect God, who is the truth.

113
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,420
And that's Jesus' summation of this issue of truth.

114
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:35,840
A challenge for us in a world of spin doctor

115
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:38,760
to live out truth and to speak truth.

116
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:42,780
And then Jesus moves on to this issue of revenge.

117
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:46,440
Revenge comes very easy to the human race.

118
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:53,580
Robin bought the lovely, revengeful game, Sorry, this past week.

119
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:54,840
You ever played Sorry?

120
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,720
It's all about revenge.

121
00:06:57,140 --> 00:06:59,480
It's all about sending somebody else backward.

122
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:02,300
It's about, I'll get even with you later.

123
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,440
You just wait, I'll get you.

124
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:06,200
That's the whole ethic behind the game.

125
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:10,360
And it's fun in a cute sense, but when you see bumper stickers like these,

126
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:18,720
do unto others before they do unto you, that's a little scary, isn't it? Shoot first, ask questions

127
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:26,370
later. You've seen that. I don't get mad. I get even. You see them on cars and trucks, but they're

128
00:07:26,370 --> 00:07:31,210
saying something. They're saying something about our ethic and society that somehow revenge is

129
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:43,130
really sweet. I like the story of the Desert Storm soldier that got one of those famous Dear John

130
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:52,300
letters. It's over. I found somebody else. Not only does she write this letter to this poor soldier

131
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:59,260
and end the relationship, but she says this, and will you return my favorite photograph of myself

132
00:07:59,260 --> 00:08:10,260
because I need it for the engagement picture in the newspaper. Brutal, isn't it? So how does he

133
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:15,990
respond? Well, the guy's devastated, and so he goes and talks to his buddies, and they all come to his

134
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:22,710
rescue. And they go through and they collect all the pictures of the whole platoons, all the guys,

135
00:08:22,810 --> 00:08:28,440
all their girlfriends' pictures, right? They collect them in a shoe box. And he sends them

136
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:37,890
back to his ex-girlfriend with this note, and I quote, please find your picture and return the

137
00:08:37,890 --> 00:08:54,180
rest to me. For the life of me, I can't remember which one you were. It's brutal, isn't it? Isn't

138
00:08:54,180 --> 00:09:01,110
that our tendency, though? When somebody insults us, we've got to strike back. We've got to get

139
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:07,570
even, whether it's physically or verbally or otherwise. It's, you know, how dare you hurt me?

140
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:16,090
You've insulted me. It's coming back at you. The challenge is this. Revenge is very easy to begin

141
00:09:16,090 --> 00:09:26,700
to escalate. One wrong done here, and the return fire is often twice as much. And the return fire

142
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:35,610
again doubles up again. And very quickly, these things escalate to unbelievable heights. See,

143
00:09:35,690 --> 00:09:40,530
a wrong gets topped by another wrong, and it builds, and it gets bigger, and the madness

144
00:09:40,530 --> 00:09:47,950
never comes to an end. The Hebrews actually had a way to stop that sort of escalation. Their concept

145
00:09:47,950 --> 00:09:50,270
was what has been written as the tooth for tooth.

146
00:09:51,770 --> 00:09:54,370
Okay, you knock out my tooth, out comes your tooth.

147
00:09:54,570 --> 00:09:56,070
Not all of your teeth.

148
00:09:57,710 --> 00:09:58,650
You see, we want to escalate.

149
00:09:58,690 --> 00:09:59,490
We want to get back.

150
00:09:59,550 --> 00:10:00,570
We want to take it to another level.

151
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:03,090
In the Hebrew concept, it goes even.

152
00:10:03,190 --> 00:10:04,510
Eye for eye, tooth for tooth.

153
00:10:04,710 --> 00:10:06,290
Equal, straight across the board.

154
00:10:06,830 --> 00:10:08,510
That's actually a fairly radical concept

155
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:10,690
because human nature escalates.

156
00:10:11,350 --> 00:10:12,970
This thing kept it even.

157
00:10:13,430 --> 00:10:17,730
But then Jesus goes even further.

158
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,820
And he writes this, or says this.

159
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:22,200
Matthew 5, 38.

160
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:26,100
You have heard the law of Moses says,

161
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,160
if an eye is injured,

162
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:28,840
injure the eye of the person who did it.

163
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,280
If a tooth gets knocked out,

164
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,020
knock out the tooth of the person who did it.

165
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:36,200
But I say, here's Jesus,

166
00:10:36,780 --> 00:10:37,620
God in the flesh,

167
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:40,560
don't resist an evil person.

168
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,440
If you're slapped on the right cheek,

169
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,320
turn the other two.

170
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:45,700
If you're ordered to court

171
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,060
and your shirt is taken from you,

172
00:10:47,620 --> 00:10:48,600
give your coat too.

173
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,620
If a soldier demands you

174
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:52,040
carry his gear for a mile,

175
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:53,460
Carry it two miles.

176
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,660
Give to those who ask.

177
00:10:56,450 --> 00:10:58,650
And don't turn away from those who want to borrow.

178
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:02,590
That's a radically different way to live, isn't it?

179
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:05,040
Boy, that really takes that retaliation

180
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,940
and kind of throws it out completely.

181
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,580
See, Jesus has a radically different approach

182
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:10,940
to the issue of grievance.

183
00:11:11,260 --> 00:11:13,060
And here's why underneath.

184
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,900
Why does he want to say these things?

185
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,680
Because if you've been following the Sermon on the Mount,

186
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,980
the kingdom heart,

187
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,700
one whose heart is filled with the love of Jesus

188
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:23,400
and for Jesus and by Jesus,

189
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:27,160
that person has already dealt with their anger,

190
00:11:27,660 --> 00:11:29,520
and as we saw recently, their contempt,

191
00:11:29,900 --> 00:11:32,600
and lust, and absorbing desire, and all those things.

192
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:36,120
And our lives are not run by those things.

193
00:11:37,540 --> 00:11:39,020
And so when a person is injured,

194
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:41,060
if you're injured in some situation,

195
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,980
your life is not the injury.

196
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:48,080
Your life is not absorbed by that event.

197
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:52,420
See, we have a larger view of our place in God's world,

198
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:56,890
and we see the person, even if they have hurt us,

199
00:11:57,530 --> 00:12:00,890
as still a creature made in the image of God,

200
00:12:01,070 --> 00:12:03,790
we see the situation through God's eyes

201
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:07,470
and we see our circumstances in light of other scriptures

202
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:08,690
that teach these things.

203
00:12:09,780 --> 00:12:12,580
Romans 8.28, we know that in all things

204
00:12:12,580 --> 00:12:15,220
God works for the good of those who love him,

205
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:18,060
who have been called according to his purpose.

206
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,560
It doesn't say everything that happens is good,

207
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:23,140
but through those things God is still working,

208
00:12:23,140 --> 00:12:24,540
God is still doing something.

209
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,580
Later in that chapter, Paul writes this

210
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:29,780
in 38 and 39 of chapter 8,

211
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,720
For I am convinced that neither death

212
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,500
nor life, angels nor demons,

213
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:35,580
the present nor the future, nor

214
00:12:35,580 --> 00:12:37,540
any powers, neither height nor depth,

215
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,720
anything else in all creation

216
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,760
can separate us from the

217
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,800
love of God that is in Christ Jesus

218
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:46,780
our Lord. See, when injury

219
00:12:46,780 --> 00:12:48,580
is seen in light of those

220
00:12:48,580 --> 00:12:50,960
realities, we realize

221
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,460
our life is bigger

222
00:12:52,460 --> 00:12:54,230
than the injury.

223
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:58,580
or the insult, or whatever it is.

224
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:04,240
I want to be careful and say a few things as cautions,

225
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:09,000
because I want us to realize that what Jesus is saying here

226
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,860
is related to the one-on-one.

227
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:13,260
This is between people.

228
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,420
This is an interpersonal kind of situation.

229
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:18,500
This is not dealing with,

230
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:21,700
should the police force take bad people off the street?

231
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:25,680
You see how very quickly that can get misapplied,

232
00:13:25,780 --> 00:13:28,540
and suddenly we're not to do any kind of restraint

233
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:30,400
of those who would do evil in a community.

234
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:31,920
This is a one-for-one issue.

235
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:36,540
This is not about the police and the army and things like that.

236
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:41,660
And the second caution I want to say is that Jesus is not laying down another set of rules.

237
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:46,780
It's easy to read Scripture and turn these principles into rules.

238
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:50,360
He is laying down great principles.

239
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,460
Great principles.

240
00:13:58,430 --> 00:14:00,010
You see, when you're operating in the kingdom of God,

241
00:14:01,850 --> 00:14:07,000
these are the types of things that a follower of Jesus does

242
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,340
because their heart is that close

243
00:14:09,340 --> 00:14:11,420
and is beating on the frequency of God's heart

244
00:14:11,420 --> 00:14:13,220
and that's how Jesus responds

245
00:14:13,220 --> 00:14:14,660
and that's how we respond to things.

246
00:14:16,830 --> 00:14:17,910
You see, you turn your other cheek,

247
00:14:18,030 --> 00:14:18,650
you give your shirt,

248
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:19,670
you go the extra mile,

249
00:14:19,750 --> 00:14:21,030
you do those kinds of things

250
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:22,830
because you love the person

251
00:14:22,830 --> 00:14:25,570
that is insulting you and so forth.

252
00:14:25,630 --> 00:14:27,410
You don't rise up and retaliate

253
00:14:27,410 --> 00:14:28,350
and bring things back.

254
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:29,930
You go a different route.

255
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:33,020
But if you read these as laws,

256
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:35,300
it's easy to also see how ridiculous it can get.

257
00:14:36,510 --> 00:14:38,090
You ever been in a third world country before?

258
00:14:38,090 --> 00:14:42,130
you know that you can step out of any restaurant

259
00:14:42,130 --> 00:14:47,930
or club or place or bazaar or whatever it is

260
00:14:47,930 --> 00:14:52,170
and you can have 50 to 100 children and adults

261
00:14:52,170 --> 00:14:55,700
begging for you to give, right?

262
00:14:57,100 --> 00:15:00,100
If you follow the ethic literally to the T

263
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:03,510
and you give everything, there you'll stand

264
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:07,030
in the square in a foreign country with nothing left

265
00:15:07,030 --> 00:15:10,540
because there'll be more people that will ask

266
00:15:10,540 --> 00:15:11,880
than you can actually even give to.

267
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:17,830
Is that what Jesus is asking us to do, is put ourselves in situations and then get stuck in Mexico?

268
00:15:19,700 --> 00:15:20,460
See, I don't think so.

269
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:30,320
If somebody is breaking into my home, and I wake up and I hear them threatening my children,

270
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:39,520
does the law that I'm reading here tell me that I'm supposed to just allow that person to beat me up and haul off my children?

271
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,540
Is that what Jesus is really saying?

272
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:45,420
You see, when you interpret those laws and you get very legalistic,

273
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:49,020
then suddenly you put yourself in some very dangerous and silly situations.

274
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:53,820
These are principles, and you're going to have to follow the Holy Spirit in this situation

275
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:57,960
to know what is the response that's of the kingdom heart in this situation.

276
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:03,820
And that, for some of us, is tricky because it doesn't give us the game plan every time.

277
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:08,260
But when you read these things, you realize Jesus is giving us principles of a kingdom heart

278
00:16:08,260 --> 00:16:09,700
and what it looks like.

279
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:15,350
Martin Luther King took these values

280
00:16:15,350 --> 00:16:20,810
and learned that you can de-escalate hatred through nonviolence.

281
00:16:22,050 --> 00:16:24,490
He learned that there were certain situations where you can do that.

282
00:16:24,770 --> 00:16:27,250
And actually, it de-escalated the situation.

283
00:16:27,970 --> 00:16:30,630
And now there are laws in the books that are just and right

284
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:32,610
because of these principles put in action.

285
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:36,180
I love the story of Richard Weaver, a Christian worker,

286
00:16:37,340 --> 00:16:39,160
who learned his living working in the mines.

287
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:44,550
And he would talk to all of his fellow miners about Jesus.

288
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:47,430
And some were really impressed and amazed,

289
00:16:47,530 --> 00:16:51,070
and others were just repulsed by his discussion about Jesus.

290
00:16:51,130 --> 00:16:53,150
And one guy says, I'm so sick of hearing about this,

291
00:16:53,370 --> 00:16:55,250
I've got a good mind to smack you in the face.

292
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:59,230
And in that situation, this gentleman said,

293
00:16:59,410 --> 00:17:02,530
if that's what you want to do, go ahead.

294
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:05,900
And he did. Clocked him. Knocked him over.

295
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:10,160
And instead of getting up and fighting, he allowed him to do it again.

296
00:17:10,860 --> 00:17:16,050
At which point, the assailant left the scene and went away.

297
00:17:16,310 --> 00:17:23,920
And the next morning when they went back to work and the gentleman, Richard Weaver, with his blows to his face still evident,

298
00:17:24,620 --> 00:17:29,140
the man who came to him crying and says, will you forgive me for what I did to you yesterday?

299
00:17:30,540 --> 00:17:35,840
Because not retaliating showed this man the reality, the seriousness of that man's faith.

300
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:38,700
And with tears in his eyes, he said, would you please forgive me?

301
00:17:39,020 --> 00:17:43,180
And he said he would, and he shared with him Jesus one more time, and he became a Christian.

302
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:45,760
In that situation,

303
00:17:46,590 --> 00:17:49,470
the reality of living that kind of ethic

304
00:17:49,470 --> 00:17:52,320
de-escalated the situation

305
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:55,630
and allowed Jesus to move in a powerful way.

306
00:17:58,640 --> 00:17:59,980
I want us to hear this carefully.

307
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:03,000
If we take Jesus' laws,

308
00:18:03,380 --> 00:18:05,700
we put ourselves in very silly and difficult

309
00:18:05,700 --> 00:18:07,680
and even dangerous situations.

310
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,980
When you take them as principles of a life heart,

311
00:18:10,280 --> 00:18:12,160
beating as Jesus' heart beats,

312
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:14,160
you begin to look for creative situations

313
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:16,800
and ways to not allow injuries to our life

314
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,020
and define our life.

315
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:21,590
We look for ways to allow God to work through us.

316
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:25,800
And if appropriate, refrain from retaliation

317
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:28,640
and instead to love the other person.

318
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:29,920
That's where Jesus goes next.

319
00:18:32,540 --> 00:18:33,780
It's beyond just revenge.

320
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,300
He now talks about enemies.

321
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:42,750
In verse 43, Jesus again says,

322
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,330
You've heard the law of Moses says,

323
00:18:44,550 --> 00:18:46,830
Love your neighbor and hate your enemy.

324
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:52,260
But I say, says Jesus, to love your enemies.

325
00:18:53,060 --> 00:18:54,880
Pray for those who persecute you.

326
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:59,240
And in that way, you'll be acting as two children of your Father in heaven.

327
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:05,380
You see, he says, for he gives his sunlight to both the evil and the good.

328
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:09,260
And he sends rain on the just and on the unjust too.

329
00:19:09,540 --> 00:19:11,880
If you love only those who love you, what good is that?

330
00:19:12,970 --> 00:19:15,230
Even corrupt tax collectors do that much.

331
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:20,700
But if you're kind only to your friends, how are you different from everyone else?

332
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:22,540
See, even pagans do that.

333
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,520
But you are to be perfect, he writes.

334
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:27,920
It says, even as your Father in heaven is perfect.

335
00:19:30,660 --> 00:19:34,940
Scribes and Pharisees of the day taught you to love your neighbor and hate your enemies.

336
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:38,500
The reality is the law of Moses did say love your neighbor,

337
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:42,840
but that hate your enemies part was kind of an interpretation thrown in there that became authoritative.

338
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,120
It was nowhere written that way.

339
00:19:47,730 --> 00:19:49,590
As the text says, loving your friends is easy.

340
00:19:50,990 --> 00:19:53,950
Loving our enemies, now that's a different issue.

341
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:58,210
We'll serve a loving God.

342
00:19:58,670 --> 00:19:59,870
That's the problem here.

343
00:19:59,870 --> 00:20:03,230
When you serve a loving God who loves everybody, good and evil alike,

344
00:20:04,430 --> 00:20:08,760
and he gives them sunshine, he gives them good waves at the beach,

345
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:13,180
beautiful snow in the mountains, they get rain, they get sunshine,

346
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:16,600
they get all the blessings that those who follow Jesus gets too.

347
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,890
If God can do that, can we do that?

348
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:30,770
See, God loves the man or the woman that is trying to take over your job at work.

349
00:20:33,470 --> 00:20:38,530
God loves the man or the woman that squares off against you on some community issue

350
00:20:38,530 --> 00:20:44,090
and that may speak against you and spread rumors even about you.

351
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:46,580
If you're a student, you'll relate to this, I hope,

352
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:51,520
that God loves the other student that ridicules you to your face

353
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:55,990
and in front of your classmates and persecutes you because of your faith.

354
00:20:59,650 --> 00:21:01,350
You may not like that person.

355
00:21:01,410 --> 00:21:02,830
You may be very angry about that person.

356
00:21:02,830 --> 00:21:05,790
You may be very angry and incensed and insulted by what they've done

357
00:21:05,790 --> 00:21:07,030
and for their persecution of you.

358
00:21:07,270 --> 00:21:11,250
But the reality is that God still loves them, even of the evil deeds they do.

359
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:16,050
He still loves them and wants them to know him and to be drawn to him.

360
00:21:16,530 --> 00:21:22,270
The highest act of love as a follower of Jesus is not to retaliate, but to pray for them.

361
00:21:23,460 --> 00:21:25,200
And how upside down is that?

362
00:21:28,710 --> 00:21:34,550
To lift them up before God and to say, I don't like them, but God, you love them.

363
00:21:34,990 --> 00:21:37,750
And I pray for their good and not for evil.

364
00:21:39,220 --> 00:21:41,500
That's the kind of people Jesus calls us to be

365
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,520
as kingdom people

366
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:45,110
that pray for their persecutors.

367
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:48,070
And our model is even Jesus on the cross.

368
00:21:48,190 --> 00:21:48,850
And I, to be honest,

369
00:21:48,930 --> 00:21:52,650
I can't barely understand or relate to this.

370
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,320
But Jesus, hanging on a cross,

371
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:59,180
nailed and bleeding and dying,

372
00:21:59,580 --> 00:22:02,280
still says, in all of that pain and agony,

373
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:03,220
still says,

374
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:04,640
forgive them, Father,

375
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:07,240
for they don't know what they're doing.

376
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,520
Can we forgive others?

377
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:19,690
when we don't believe they know what they're doing?

378
00:22:22,260 --> 00:22:25,580
Can we pray for our enemies even when they persecute us?

379
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:29,240
Because God still wants to reach them

380
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:30,960
and do something through them and bring them to himself.

381
00:22:33,610 --> 00:22:35,390
The final challenge Jesus gives us

382
00:22:35,390 --> 00:22:39,450
is that God wants his followers to be mature and complete.

383
00:22:39,710 --> 00:22:40,930
Perfect, says the Bible.

384
00:22:42,140 --> 00:22:44,220
And that word perfect, when you get underneath it

385
00:22:44,220 --> 00:22:45,460
and look at the original language,

386
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:49,260
it has that idea of maturing, of completing something to the end.

387
00:22:50,610 --> 00:22:52,250
And I'm challenged that Jesus is saying,

388
00:22:52,250 --> 00:22:54,590
you know, in every area of life, you can always go a little higher,

389
00:22:54,930 --> 00:22:56,210
you can stretch a little further,

390
00:22:56,510 --> 00:22:58,470
you can be like me a little bit more.

391
00:22:59,390 --> 00:23:01,090
And all of your life is to be given

392
00:23:01,090 --> 00:23:04,860
in following Jesus and maturing in Him.

393
00:23:06,090 --> 00:23:08,590
And when He finally comes, when we finally meet Him face to face,

394
00:23:09,170 --> 00:23:10,110
we're perfected then.

395
00:23:12,170 --> 00:23:12,970
Oh, that'll be fun.

396
00:23:15,890 --> 00:23:17,110
So I want to conclude with this.

397
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:20,720
When the Spirit of God, friends, is released in us,

398
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:24,100
and fanned into fire, when it's fanned into flame,

399
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:30,500
We begin to exhibit the kinds of behaviors and the attitudes that Jesus is talking about.

400
00:23:31,180 --> 00:23:32,660
It cuts up against our culture.

401
00:23:32,980 --> 00:23:37,120
It cuts up against, in many ways, the way perhaps we've been raised or taught to deal with situations.

402
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:42,200
But we begin to allow the heart of Jesus to overtake our own heart

403
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:47,980
and to make it soft and supple like the Lord's, even for the enemies of the Lord.

404
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,220
Jesus said, forgive them for they don't know what they do.

405
00:23:51,220 --> 00:23:56,500
and as we begin to allow that fire to burn in us

406
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:57,480
and to soften us

407
00:23:57,480 --> 00:24:00,460
and we see our lives as larger than the injuries

408
00:24:00,460 --> 00:24:01,700
or the issues in our life

409
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,280
but to see it from God's perspective

410
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:07,740
then hopefully our lives begin to embody the truths

411
00:24:07,740 --> 00:24:10,000
in this famous passage I'm going to conclude with

412
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:13,120
and it's from 1 Corinthians chapter 13

413
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:15,830
and I want to say it's too bad

414
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:18,130
that the only times we tend to see this verse

415
00:24:18,130 --> 00:24:19,330
are in weddings

416
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:24,960
we so often see this verse in light of romantic love

417
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:26,820
I think that's appropriate.

418
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:29,500
But I think it goes deeper than just romantic love.

419
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:35,160
This is a description of Jesus' love expressed through us in the world,

420
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:37,660
in a variety of circumstances.

421
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,360
Here's what it looks like again.

422
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:43,560
1 Corinthians 13, starting in verse 4.

423
00:24:44,780 --> 00:24:49,620
Love is patient and kind.

424
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:56,800
Love is not jealous or boastful or proud or rude.

425
00:24:58,040 --> 00:25:00,880
It does not demand its own way.

426
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:03,600
Love is not irritable,

427
00:25:04,230 --> 00:25:06,810
and it keeps no record of when it has been wronged.

428
00:25:06,810 --> 00:25:10,220
It is never glad about injustice,

429
00:25:10,940 --> 00:25:13,540
but rejoices whenever the truth wins out.

430
00:25:15,060 --> 00:25:16,280
Love never gives up,

431
00:25:17,030 --> 00:25:18,190
never loses faith,

432
00:25:18,730 --> 00:25:19,890
is always hopeful,

433
00:25:20,630 --> 00:25:23,030
and endures through every circumstance.

434
00:25:25,180 --> 00:25:26,120
It's the kingdom ethic.

435
00:25:27,130 --> 00:25:27,750
It's love.

436
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:31,540
The challenge is the same as last week.

437
00:25:31,540 --> 00:25:34,520
where is God challenging you to grow

438
00:25:34,520 --> 00:25:36,790
in some area of these issues

439
00:25:36,790 --> 00:25:38,750
of truth, of enemies,

440
00:25:39,050 --> 00:25:40,490
of retaliation, revenge.

441
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:42,540
And I would just ask again,

442
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,760
how can we help you?

443
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:45,600
Write us a note.

444
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:46,320
Give us a call.

445
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:46,860
Let me know.

446
00:25:47,100 --> 00:25:48,080
Let's spend some time together.

447
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:50,120
Let's talk about our lives for real

448
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:51,380
that we might allow the Spirit

449
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:53,620
to develop these values,

450
00:25:54,180 --> 00:25:55,020
these behaviors.

451
00:25:56,770 --> 00:25:57,270
And friends,

452
00:25:58,030 --> 00:25:59,910
this is life on a whole different plane.

453
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:02,300
And it's good.

454
00:26:03,220 --> 00:26:03,920
It's not easy.

455
00:26:04,260 --> 00:26:05,670
but it is good.

456
00:26:06,590 --> 00:26:08,270
It's fulfilling in a whole different way.

457
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,680
It's exciting to live like this.

458
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:12,700
It's challenging.

459
00:26:14,860 --> 00:26:17,260
And deep down you'll know that it's right.

460
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:19,780
That's how we were created to live.

461
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:22,020
So let us go there.

462
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:23,760
Father, I pray,

463
00:26:25,490 --> 00:26:26,890
as we wrap up this message

464
00:26:26,890 --> 00:26:29,990
and look at the reality of these issues in our lives,

465
00:26:32,130 --> 00:26:33,350
that Lord, we'd not make them laws,

466
00:26:33,350 --> 00:26:35,450
but make them the principles that guide us,

467
00:26:36,050 --> 00:26:38,890
and that we live them out in concrete and creative ways

468
00:26:38,890 --> 00:26:40,130
in real situations.

469
00:26:41,360 --> 00:26:43,540
Because we're that close to your spirit.

470
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:49,150
Because the spirit is that much just filling us up and leading us.

471
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:57,330
That we become the kind of people that live out these examples that Jesus gives of a kingdom heart.

472
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:05,050
Help us, I pray, to be these upside down kingdom kind of people.

473
00:27:05,490 --> 00:27:13,180
That by your spirit are released in a community to change it.

474
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:17,200
To bring peace and truth and love.

475
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:21,450
where there is discord and pain and sorrow.

476
00:27:23,650 --> 00:27:25,110
And that by these actions, Father,

477
00:27:25,110 --> 00:27:27,910
that the community would know that you are the truth

478
00:27:27,910 --> 00:27:29,840
and would find you.

479
00:27:32,590 --> 00:27:33,590
So help us, dear Lord,

480
00:27:33,750 --> 00:27:35,610
to confess whatever we need to confess,

481
00:27:36,130 --> 00:27:39,330
to give you whatever we have struggled with

482
00:27:39,330 --> 00:27:41,690
and allow you to take us to a new place.

483
00:27:44,010 --> 00:27:45,390
Make us mature, we pray.

484
00:27:46,630 --> 00:27:48,490
May these scriptures become real in our lives.

485
00:27:48,590 --> 00:27:50,430
May we be mature believers

486
00:27:50,430 --> 00:27:53,800
that day by day are getting a little bit more like Jesus.

487
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:56,520
a little more filled up with his love,

488
00:27:57,540 --> 00:27:59,000
a little more sensitive to your spirit.

489
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,340
And day by day, people will see that you are truth,

490
00:28:03,420 --> 00:28:06,260
you are real, and they would be drawn to you

491
00:28:06,260 --> 00:28:09,440
because of what you're doing in our lives.

492
00:28:11,230 --> 00:28:12,990
Thank you, Father, that you've redeemed us,

493
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:16,660
cleaned us up, filled us up for service,

494
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:17,660
and sent us out.

495
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:21,400
And I pray that Fullerton would be a faithful,

496
00:28:23,690 --> 00:28:28,690
godly community of people that live upside down,

497
00:28:28,970 --> 00:28:34,450
that really live right side up in an upside down world.

498
00:28:34,450 --> 00:28:39,120
May these kingdom values become ours

499
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:43,210
because they're all about your heart

500
00:28:43,210 --> 00:28:44,350
and your character.

501
00:28:44,930 --> 00:28:46,500
They reflect your goodness.

502
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:50,080
Thanks for the challenge to a new way to live.

503
00:28:51,670 --> 00:28:52,250
We love you.

504
